The Chronicle Fungai Muderere, Senior Sports Reporter
DELTA Beverages Lagers Pool Club beat police side Donnington to clinch the first prize in the Bulawayo Central Business District League Super 8 tournament that was played on Saturday at Golden Pillar, a venue popularly known as KwaDziko. The Adam Machakwa-led Delta Beverages demolished Donnington 5-3 to take a prize-money of US$100 home while the latter got US$60. In a third place playoff, another police outfit Bulawayo Central thumped Ekasi 5-0 and got US$30.  Ekasi got US$20 while Mash Restoration, Mpumelelo, Nokkies and Expendables came out on position five, six, seven and eight respectable. Central Business District Pool League chairman Aburekwi Mazikita said they were happy that they hosted a successful tournament. <img class="wp-image-616108 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-59-4.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-59-4.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/06/Untitled-59-4-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zimbabwe Pool Association (Zipa) “It was indeed a surprise win for Delta because no one expected them to shine. The turnout was very pleasing and the contest was played in true sportsmanship. We are looking forward to having a similar tournament where we will give the other eight members of our 16-member league a chance to compete against each other. It is always good to have such pre-season tournaments to help our players to continue sharpening their skills,” said —  @FungaiMuderere